{"id":"280912340_Hypergraph_coloring_up_to_condensation","abstract":"Improving a result of Dyer, Frieze and Greenhill [Journal of Combinatorial\nTheory, Series B, 2015], we determine the $q$-colorability threshold in random\n$k$-uniform hypergraphs up to an additive error of $\\ln 2+\\varepsilon_q$, where\n$\\lim_{q\\to\\infty}\\varepsilon_q=0$. The new lower bound on the threshold\nmatches the \"condensation phase transition\" predicted by statistical physics\nconsiderations [Krzakala et al., PNAS~2007].","authors":["Peter Ayre","Amin Coja-Oghlan","Catherine Greenhill"],"meta":["July 2019Random Structures and Algorithms 54(4)","DOI:10.1002/rsa.20824","SourcearXiv"],"references":["236202777_Chasing_the_K-Colorability_Threshold","313609388_On_the_evolution_of_random_graphs","282564228_The_satisfiability_threshold_for_k-XORSAT","274514765_Colorings_of_Partial_Steiner_Systems_and_Their_Applications","268496537_Random_Graphs","267760132_Proof_of_the_Satisfiability_Conjecture_for_Large_k","262158441_Sharp_thresholds_for_constraint_satisfaction_problems_and_homomorphisms","236589486_Upper-Bounding_the_k-Colorability_Threshold_by_Counting_Covers","231246650_The_Nature_of_the_Glassy_State_and_the_Behavior_of_Liquids_at_Low_Temperature","230609116_On_the_chromatic_number_of_a_random_hypergraph","226926475_Random_k-Sat_A_Tight_Threshold_For_Moderately_Growing_k","227315806_The_chromatic_number_of_random_graphs","226558379_The_chromatic_number_of_random_graphs","226132597_Expose-and-merge_exploration_and_the_chromatic_number_of_a_random_graph","225638772_Sharp_concentration_of_the_chromatic_number_on_random_graphsGn_p"]}